The paper proposes a variable decomposition algorithm for dense Gaussian process regression that makes it practical for large scale problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions empirical comparisons against competing methods like Conjugate Gradient or SMO, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the handling of datasets with 100,000 samples or more, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of scalable systems (cs.SI).
